      "number": 1,
      "id": "PR_kwDOTTrAgM7v9udx",
      "title": "Remove nonce claim from OAT",
      "url": "https://github.com/gffletch/openid_authn_token/pull/1",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "josephdecock",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "I'm not sure why the OAT carries the Source ID Token's `nonce` claim. The `nonce` is a request-response correlator between the Requesting Client and the OP. Is there a use case where a Target RP would need it?\r\n\r\nThis PR removes `nonce` from the OAT claims and adds a brief note in Security Considerations as a way to surface the question. My thinking is that session correlation and replay detection are already covered by `sid`, `jti`, `exp`, and proof-of-possession, but I may be missing something.",
